  "text": "• Negotiation strategy. Credentials grant parties different choices with respect to what release (or ask) the counterpart and when to do it, thus allowing for multiple trust negotiation strategies [CITATION_1] . For instance, an eager strategy, requires parties to turn over all their credentials if the release policy for them is satisfied, without waiting for the credentials to be requested. By contrast, a parsimonious strategy requires that parties only release credentials upon explicit request by the server (avoiding unnecessary releases).",
